tldr: The user requested to implement a database, an admin dashboard, and
  authentication for a sleep questionnaire application based on a Statement of
  Work. The project involved updating demographics, creating a Prisma model for
  responses, building API routes for data management, and setting up a simple
  middleware-based authentication system for the admin dashboard.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  adding a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for data access,
  and an authentication system. The approach involved first updating the
  demographic fields in the questionnaire to align with the SOW, then defining a
   model in Prisma. Key decisions included using NeonDB
  for the PostgreSQL database due to its compatibility and simplicity, and
  opting for a simple password-based authentication with Next.js middleware for
  the admin dashboard. API routes were developed for saving questionnaire
  submissions, retrieving all responses, and exporting data as a CSV. An admin
  login page and a dashboard to view responses were also created. During
  testing, all API endpoints and the authentication flow were confirmed to be
  fully functional, although a minor UI interaction for form submission was
  noted.
